
WebHooks :
1. New Item -> Name -> Pipeline -> Ok
2. Configure -> pipeline-> Hello World Script -> Apply -> Save -> Build
3. Configure -> Pipeline -> Syntax -> Sample Step -> Git checkout -> Git URL -> Credentials* -> Main branch -> generate Script ID -> paste script id inplace of Echo "Hello World" -> Apply -> Save -> Build 
Credentials -> Github Settings - > Developer options -> Tokens Classic -> Generate a Classic Token -> Check all boxes and set a limited timer -> Use this as pwd and Github username as username
4. CMD in system and type -> ngrok http <port same as jenkins> -> Copy forwarding link 
5. Git repo settings -> Webhooks -> Create a webhook -> In payload URL -> paste ngrok link : https://ngrok......com/github-webhook/
6. In Jenkins - > Configuration -> Triggers -> GitHub Trigger -> check the box 
7. Make a new commit in repo and Build will automatically start
